Start off by installing the python libraries below if not installed already.

Install pygame #https://www.pygame.org/wiki/GettingStarted
Install scikit-learn #https://scikit-learn.org/1.5/getting_started.html
Install pytorch #https://pytorch.org/get-started/locally/
Install pandas #https://pandas.pydata.org/docs/getting_started/install.html
Install numpy #https://numpy.org/install/

This is an implementation of a card coutning Ai with the use of 1 Deck.
To run the game and play without the AI agent, type "python .\Blackjack.py -standard" or simply "python .\Blackjack.py"
into the terminal, while being inside the corresponding file directory.
Otherwise,
To run the game and play with the AI agent, type "python .\Blackjack.py -ai" 
into the terminal, while being inside the corresponding file directory.
